article.description: Mississippi Valley St. 64, Prairie View A&M 61
article.headline: Mississippi Valley St. 64, Prairie View A&M 61
article.linkText: Mississippi Valley St. 64, Prairie View A&M 61
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. (AP) -- Richard Cannon scored 17 points and Mississippi Valley State sent Prairie View A&M to its sixth straight Southwestern Athletic Conference loss with a 64-61 win on Saturday. The game was decided at the free-throw line where Mississippi Valley (7-11, 4-2 SWAC) took 36 shots to Prairie View's 12. The Delta Devils made 21 of their free throws, making up for an eight-point performance from leading scorer Stanford Speech. Prairie View (2-16, 0-6) was called for 28 fouls compared to Mississippi Valley's 12. The Panthers were led by Brian Ezeh's 17 and got 11 points from Andy Genao. The Delta Devils, who led 27-22 at halftime, also got 11 points each from Michael Clark and Kadrian Bryant.
